comment.@value: Property \"unit\" specifies the appropriate unit of measure.
Class \"AcquisitionMode\" is a type of microscopy performed for each channel.
Class \"AffineTransform\" is a matrix used to transform the shape. The element has 6 xsd:float attributes. If the element is present then all 6 values must be included.
Class \"Annotation\" is an annotation from which all others are ultimately derived.
Class \"Arc\" is various kinds of Arc lamps.
Class \"ArcType\" is the type of Arc lamps - Hg, Xe, HgXe.
Class \"BasicAnnotation\" is an abstract Basic Annotation from which some others are derived.
Class \"BinData\" is contents of this element are base64-encoded.
Class \"BinaryFile\" is binary files.
Class \"Binning\" is numbers of pixels that are combined to form larger pixels. {used:CCD,EMCCD}.
Class \"BooleanAnnotation\" is simple boolean annotations of type xsd:boolean.
Class \"Channel\" is channels in the Image, even for a single-plane image.
Class \"Color\" is colrs. The value is an integer between -2,147,483,648 and 2,147,483,647 (inclusive). The value is a signed 32 bit encoding of RGBA so \"-1\" is #FFFFFFFF or solid white.
Class \"CommentAnnotation\" is simple comment annotations.
Class \"Compression\" is compression schemes used to encode the data.
Class \"ContrastMethod\" is the techniques used to achieve contrast for each channel.
Class \"Correction\" is the collections applied to the lens.
Class \"Dataset\" is collections of images that are always processed together. Images can belong to more than one Dataset, and a Dataset may contain more than one Image.
Class \"Detector\" is types of detectors used to capture the image.
Class \"DetectorSettings\" is settings applied to a detector as well as a reference to the detector.
Class \"DetectorType\" is the types of detectors. E.g. CCD, PMT, EMCCD etc.
Class \"Dichroic\" is dichromatic beamsplitters or dichroic mirrors used for this filter combination.
Class \"DimensionOrder\" is the orders in which the individual planes of data are interleaved.
Class \"DoubleAnnotation\" is simple numerical annotations of type xsd:double.
Class \"Ellipse\" is simple ellipse objects. If rotation is required apply a transformation at the Shape level.
Class \"EmissionFilter\" is a filter placed in the Emission light path.
Class \"ExcitationFilter\" is a filter placed in the Excitation light path.
Class \"Experiment\" is experiments.
Class \"ExperimentType\" is the types of experiments.

Class \"ExperimenterGroup\" is groups of experimenters. The information should ideally be specified for at least one Leader as a contact for the group. The Leaders are themselves Experimenters.the types of experiments.

Class \"External\" is a file location. Can optionally specify a portion of a file using Offset and a ReadLength. If Offset and ReadLength are specified in conjuction with Compression, then they point into the uncompressed file.
Class \"Filament\" is various kinds of filament bulbs such as Incadescent or Halogen.
Class \"FilamentType\" is the types of filaments.
Class \"FileAnnotation\" is file object annotations.
Class \"FillRule\" is fill ruless.

Class \"Filter\" is filters. A filter is either an excitation or emission filters. There should be one filter element specified per wavelength in the image. The channel number associated with a filter set is specified in Channel. It is based on the FilterSpec type, so has the required attributes Manufacturer, Model, and LotNumber.
Class \"FilterSet\" is filter set manufacturer specifications.
Class \"FilterType\" is the types of filters.

Class \"Folder\" is possibly heterogeneous collections of data. Folders may contain Folders so that data may be organized within a tree of Folders. Data may be in multiple Folders but a Folder may not be in more than one other Folder.
Class \"Font\" is fonts used to draw the texts.
Class \"FontFamily\" is font families used to draw the texts.
Class \"FontStyle\" is font styles used to draw the texts.
Class \"GenericExcitationSource\" is sources as collections of key/value pairs, stored in Maps. The other lightsource objects should always be used in preference to this if possible..
Class \"IlluminationType\" is methods of illumination used to capture the channel.
Class \"Image\" is actual images and their meta-data.
Class \"ImageFile\" is actual image files.
Class \"ImagingCondition\" is image conditions introduced in the OWL ontology.
Class \"ImagingEnvironment\" is environments that the biological samples were in during the experiments.
Class \"Immersion\" is immersion mediums the lens are designed for.

Class \"Instrument\" is instruments used to capture the Images. It is primarily a container for manufacturer\'s model and catalog numbers for the Microscope, LightSource, Detector, Objective and Filters components.
Class \"Label\" is text labels. Any transformation should be applied at the shape level.
Class \"Laser\" is laser.
Class \"LaserMedium\" is actual lasing mediums for given laser types.
Class \"LaserType\" is a laser type.
Class \"LightEmittingDiode\" is various kinds of LED lamps.
Class \"LightPath\" is light paths.
Class \"LightSource\" is light sources for the instruments.
Class \"LightSourceSettings\" is settings of light sources for the instruments.
Class \"Line\" is straight lines defined by their end points.
Class \"ListAnnotation\" is groups of annotation objects. It uses the sequence of annotation refs from the base Annotation to form the list.
Class \"LongAnnotation\" is simple numerical annotations of type xsd:long
Class \"Manufacturer\" is manufacturers of the components.

Class \"ManufacturerSpec\" is the base from which many microscope components are extended. E.g Objective, Filter etc. Provides attributes for recording common properties of these components such as Manufacturer name, Model etc, all of which are optional.
Class \"Map\" is mappings of key/value pairs.
Class \"MapAnnotation\" is map annotations. The contents of this is a list of key/value pairs.
Class \"Marker\" is shapes of marker on the ends of lines.

Class \"Mask\" is masks. A mask ROI shape is a link to a BinData object that is a BIT mask drawn on top of the image as an ROI. It is applied at the same scale, pixel to pixel, as the Image the ROI is applied to, unless a transform is applied at the shape level.shapes of marker on the ends of lines.
Class \"Medium\" is the mediums used for lenses.
Class \"MicrobeamManipulation\" is microbeam operation types and the regions of the images.
Class \"Microscope\" is microscopes\' manufacturer specifications.
Class \"MicroscopeType\" is a type of microscope.
Class \"NamingConvention\" is predefined lists of values for the well labels.
Class \"NumericAnnotation\" is an abstract Numeric Annotation from which some others are derived.
Class \"Objective\" is microscopes\' objective lens.
Class \"ObjectiveMedium\" is a description of a Medium used for the lens. The Medium is the actual immersion medium used in this case.
Class \"ObjectiveSettings\" is settings applied to an objective as well as a reference to the objective.
Class \"PixelType\" is numbers size/kind used to represent pixels.
Class \"Pixels\" is pixels. Pixels is going to be removed in the future, but it is still required.
Class \"Plane\" is microscope stages and image timing data for given channels/z-sections/timepoints.

Class \"Plate\" is microtiter plates within a screen. A plate can belong to more than one screen. The Screen(s) that a plate belongs to are specified by the ScreenRef element. The Plate ID and Name attributes are required.The Wells in a plate are numbers from the top-left corner in a grid starting at zero. i.e. The top-left well of a plate is index (0,0).

Class \"PlateAcquisition\" is single acquisition runs for plates. This object is used to record the set of images acquired in a single acquisition run. The Images for this run are linked to PlateAcquisition through WellSample.
Class \"Point\" is points.
Class \"Polygon\" is closed shapes formed of straight lines. Note: Polygon uses counterclockwise winding (this is the default OpenGL behavior).
Class \"Polyline\" is  open shapes formed of straight lines. Note: Polyline uses counterclockwise winding (this is the default OpenGL behavior).

Class \"Project\" is projects. Datasets can be grouped into projects using a many-to-many relationship. A Dataset may belong to one or more Projects. Projects do not directly contain images - only by virtue of containing datasets, which themselves contain images.
Class \"Protocol\" is screen protocols.
Class \"Pulse\" is the pulse modes of the lasers.
Class \"Pump\" is references to the light sources.  It is used within the Laser element to specify the light source for the laser\'s pump (if any).
Class \"Reagent\" is chemical or some other physical experimental parameters.
Class \"ReagentSet\" is sets of reagents; may contain very detailed information toreproduce some of that information found in a screening database.
Class \"Rectangle\" is simple rectangle objects. If rotation is required apply a transformation at the Shape level.

Class \"RigionOfInterest\" is four dimensional \'Region of Interests\'. If they are not used, and the Image has more than one plane, the entire set of planes is assumed to be included in the ROI. Multiple ROIs may be specified.
Class \"Rights\" is the rights holder of the data and the rights held.
Class \"Screen\" is groupings for Plates.
Class \"ScreenType\" is the type of the Screen.
Class \"Settings\" is a super class of \"DetectorSettings\", \"LightSourceSettings\" and \"ObjectiveSettings\".
Class \"Shape\" is single specific ROI shapes and links that to any channels, and timepoints and z-sections. It alsorecords any transform applied to the ROI shape.
Class \"StageLabel\" is used to specify a name and position for a stage position in the microscope\'s reference frame.
Class \"StructuredAnnotations\" is unordered collections of annotations attached to objects in the OME data model.
Class \"TagAnnotation\" is a tag annotation (represents a tag or a tagset).
Class \"TermAnnotation\" is tag annotations. A tag annotation represents a tag or a tagset.
Class \"TextAnnotation\" is an abstract Text Annotation from which some others are derived.
Class \"TiffData\" is locations of the pixel data in tiff files.
Class \"TimestampAnnotation\" is date/time annotations of type xsd:dateTime
Class \"TransmittanceRange\" is ranges of wavelengths that are transmitted by the filters. It also records the maximum amount of light transmitted.
Class \"TypeAnnotation\" is an abstract Type Annotation from which some others are derived.

Class \"Well\" is components of the Well/Plate/Screen constructs to describe screening applications. A Well has a number of WellSample elements that link to the Images collected in this well. The ReagentRef links any Reagents that were used in this Well. A well is part of only one Plate. The origin for the row and column identifiers is the top left corner of the plate starting at zero. i.e The top left well of a plate is index (0,0).
Class \"WellSample\" is individual images that have been captured within Wells.
Class \"XMLAnnotation\" is general xml annotations. The contents of this is not processed as OME XML but should still be well-formed XML.
Property \"acquisitionMode\" specifies the acquisition mode that describes the type of microscopy performed for each channel.
Property \"airPressure\" specifies the air pressure which is the define units.
Property \"annotation\" specifies an annotation from which all others are ultimately derived.
Property \"annotator\" specifies the person who attached this annotation.  e.g. If UserA annotates something with TagB, owned by UserB, UserA is still the Annotator.
Property \"arcType\" specifies the type of the arc.
Property \"binaryFile\" specifies the binary file.
Property \"binning\" specifies the binning data that represents the number of pixels combined to form larger pixels.
Property \"channel\" speficies the channel.
Property \"color\" speficies the color, such as the color used to reder the channel and the marker color used to highlight the well.
Property \"compression\" specifies the compression scheme used to encode the data.
Property \"contrastMethod\" specifies the technique used to achieve contrast for each channel.
Property \"correction\" specifies the correction applied to the lens.
Property \"cutIn\" speficies the wavelength below which there is less than 50% transmittance for a filter.
Property \"cutInTolerance\" speficies the cutIn tolerance.
Property \"cutOut\" speficies the wavelength above which there is less than 50% transmittance for a filter.
Property \"cutOutTolerance\" speficies the cutOut tolerance.
Property \"dataset\" specifies a collection of images that are always processed together.
Property \"deltaT\" specifies time since the beginning of the experiment.
Property \"detectorType\" specifies the type of the detector.
Property \"dichroic\" specifies the dichromatic beamsplitter or dichroic mirror used for this filter combination.
Property \"dimensionOrder\" specifies the order in which the individual planes of data are interleaved.
Property \"emissionFilter\" specifies the filters placed in the emission light path.
Property \"emissionWavelength\" specifies the wavelength of emission for a particular channel.
Property \"excitationFilter\" specifies the filters placed in the excitation light path.
Property \"excitationWavelength\" spefifies the wavelength of excitation for a particular channel.
Property \"experiment\" specifies the experiment.
Property \"experimentType\" specifies the type of experiment.
Property \"experimenter\" specifies the person performed an imaging experiment.
Property \"experimenterGroup\" specifies the group of experimenters who performed an imaging experiment.
Property \"exposureTime\" specifies the length of the exposure.
Property \"external\" specifies the file location.
Property \"fillColor\" specifies the color of the fill.
Property \"fillRule\" specifies the rule used to decide which parts of the shape to fill.
Property \"filterType\" specifies the type of the filter.
Property \"folder\" specifies a folder which is a possibly heterogeneous collection of data.
Property \"font\" specifies the font used to draw the text.
Property \"fonfFamily\" specifies the font family used to draw the text.
Property \"fontSize\" specifies the size of the font.
Property \"fontStyle\" specifies the style and weight applied to the text.
Property \"humidity\" specifies the humidity around the sample.
Property \"illuminationType\" specifies the method illumination used to capture the channel.
Property \"image\" specifies the actual image.
Property \"imageFile\" specifies the actual image file.
Property \"imagingCondition\" specifies the imaging condition.
Property \"imagingEnvironment\" specifies the environment that the biological sample was in during the experiment.
Property \"immersion\" specifies the immersion medium the lens is designed for.
Property \"laserMedium\" specifies the Medium attribute specifies the actual lasing medium for a given laser type.
Property \"laserType\" specifies the type of laser.
Property \"leader\" specifies an experimenter group leader.
Property \"manufacturer\" specifies the manufacturer of the component.
Property \"manufacturerSpec\" specifies the base from which many microscope components are extended.
Property \"map\" specifies the value of the map that contains of a list of key/value pairs.
Property \"markerEnd\" specifies the end of the marker.
Property \"markerStart\" specifies the start of the marker.
Property \"medium\" specifies a medium used for the lens.
Property \"microbeamManipulation\" specifies the microbeam operation that describes a microbeam operation type and the region of the image it was applied to.
Property \"microscope\" specifies the microscope.
Property \"microscopeType\" specifies the type of the microscope.
Property \"mimeType\" specifies the MIME type of the binary file.
Property \"objectiveSettings\" specifies the physical size of a pixel.
Property \"physicalSizeX\" specifies the physical size of a pixel on the x axis.
Property \"physicalSizeY\" specifies the physical size of a pixel on the y axis.
Property \"physicalSizeZ\" specifies the physical size of a pixel on the z axis.
Property \"pinholeSize\" specifies the adjustable pin hole diameters for confocal microscopes.
Property \"pixcelType\" specifies the number size/kind used to represent a pixel.
Property \"pixels\" specifies the pixels of the image.
Property \"plane\" specifies the microscope stage and image timing data for a given channel/z-section/timepoint.
Property \"plate\" specifies a microtiter plate within the screen.
Property \"plateAcquisition\" specifies the plate qcquisition that describes a single acquisition run for a plate.
Property \"point\" specifies the point.
Property \"positionX\" specifies the x position of the stage.
Property \"positionY\" specifies the y position of the stage.
Property \"positionZ\" specifies the z position of the stage.
Property \"power\" specifies the light-source power.
Property \"protocol\" specifies the protocol such as the screen protocol.
Property \"pulse\" specifies the pulse mode of the laser.
Property \"pump\" specifies the pump of the laser.
Property \"readOutRate\" specifies the speed at which the detector can count pixels. {used:CCD,EMCCD}  This is the bytes per second that can be read from the detector (like a baud rate).
Property \"reagent\" specifies the reagent that describes a chemical or some other physical experimental parameters.
Property \"reagentSet\" specifies a set of reagents.
Property \"regionOfInterest\" specifies a four dimensional region of interest (ROI).
Property \"repetitionRate\" specifies the rate in Hz at which the laser pulses if the Pulse type is \'Repetitive\'.
Property \"screenType\" specifies the screen type.
Property \"shape\" specifies the shape that contains a single specific ROI shape and links that to any channels, and a timepoint and a z-section.
Property \"stageLabel\" specifies the stage labe which is a name and position for a stage position in the microscope\'s reference frame.
Property \"strokeColor\" specifies the color of stroke.
Property \"strokeWidth\" specifies the width of the stroke.
Property \"temperature\" specifies the temperature.
Property \"tiffData\" specifies the location of the pixel data in a tiff file.
Property \"timeIncrement\" specifies the timeinclement that is used for time series that have a global timing specification instead of per-timepoint timing information.
Property \"transform\" specifies a matrix used to transform the shape.
Property \"transmittanceRange\" specifies the transmittance range that describes wavelengths that are transmitted by the filter.
Property \"union\" specifies the union of sets.
Property \"voltage\" specifies the voltage of the detector.
Property \"waveLength\" specifies the wave length of the laser.
Property \"well\" specifies the well which is a component of the well/plate/screen construct to describe screening applications.
Property \"li\" specifies an element of the Bag.
Property \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/depicts\" specifies a relationship between the image and something that the image depicts.
Property \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/thumnail\" specifies  a relationship between a full-size image and a smaller, representative image that has been derrived from it.
